impair /ɪmˈpɛə/

(impairing,impaired,impairs) 

1. V-T If something impairs something such as an ability or the way something works, it damages it or makes it worse. 损害 [正式] 

例： Consumption of alcohol impairs your ability to drive a car or operate machinery. 饮酒会削弱你驾驶汽车或操纵机器的能力。 

2. impaired ADJ 受损的 

例： The blast left him with permanently impaired hearing. 爆炸造成了他永久性听力损伤。

